HEADWORD: Unhouse
<hw>Un*house"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>house</ets>.]</ety> <def>To drive from a house or
habitation; to dislodge; hence, to deprive of shelter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

